nodes.bodyText:
I would add this, but it depends on the purpose of the test - if deadlock was acceptable result, then this would only break the test:
        List<Runnable> notExecutedYet = executor.shutdownNow();
        assertTrue("some jobs never executed: " + notExecutedYet.size(), notExecutedYet.isEmpty());

It will fail if the executor pool is so small that it can execute some of tasks and some must wait in a queue. If tasks are not ending, the pool will not be capable to run more ...
So now we have 60 threads in pool for 300 tasks (3*100). Easy.

